	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs8498B7A6">WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csAC81313F"><span class="csB9803513">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 5177</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates G. Howell, Masters, Burkhammer, Jennings, Fehrenbacher, Hillenbrand, Heckert, Green, Canterbury, Campbell, and Hite</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced February 04, 2026; referred to the Committee on Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;11-15C-1, &sect;11-15C-2, &sect;11-15C-3, &sect;11-15C-4, &sect;11-15C-5, &sect;11-15C-6, &sect;11-15C-7, &sect;11-15C-8, &sect;11-15C-9, and &sect;11-15C-10, relating to creating a state sales tax rebate for qualifying materials used in the construction of modest homes of 1,600 square feet or less, to limit the rebate to the state six percent sales tax, to permit voluntary municipal participation, to establish fixed material quantity limits, to require in state purchasing and affidavits, and to grant rule making and inspection authority to the State Tax Department.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">article 15C. rebate for qualified building material and inspection costs.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-1. Legislative findings.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The Legislature finds that West Virginia faces a shortage of modest housing and that the state consumers sales and service tax increases construction costs. The Legislature further finds that a narrowly tailored rebate of the state portion of the sales tax tied to defined material quantities, in state purchases, and inspections will promote housing construction while protecting the tax base and supporting West Virginia suppliers.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-2. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">For purposes of this article:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) &quot;Eligible modest dwelling&quot; means a newly constructed detached single family residence located in West Virginia that meets all of the following requirements:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Heated living space of 1,600 square feet or less above grade</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) A basement is optional -- If constructed, the basement shall be unfinished and excluded from heated living space;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) A lot size of not less than 0.5 acre and not more than 1.0 acre;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Standard stock windows and doors only &ndash; custom sizes are excluded; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Constructed for retail sale and sold to an end purchaser.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) &quot;Builder&quot; means a person or entity licensed to do business in West Virginia that constructs an eligible modest dwelling for retail sale.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) &quot;In state supplier&quot; means a seller with a physical place of business located in West Virginia that collects and remits West Virginia sales tax.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) &quot;Eligible materials&quot; means only those materials listed in &sect;11-15C-6 of this code, purchased within the stated quantity limits and incorporated into the eligible modest dwelling.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-3. State sales tax rebate created.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A builder may apply for a rebate equal to the state six percent consumers sales and service tax paid on eligible materials.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The rebate applies only to the state portion of the tax. Municipal sales taxes are excluded unless a municipality voluntarily participates under &sect;11-15C-4 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The rebate may be claimed only after the dwelling is sold, inspected, and all documentation is approved.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-4. Voluntary municipal participation.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A municipality that imposes a municipal sales tax may elect to participate in this program by ordinance.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) A participating municipality may authorize a rebate of all or part of its municipal sales tax on eligible materials.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The State Tax Department shall administer any municipal rebate authorized under this section.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-5. Purchase and documentation requirements.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) All eligible materials must be purchased from an in state supplier.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Itemized receipts showing West Virginia sales tax paid are required.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Records must be retained for 60 months from the date the rebate is issued.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Materials purchased from out of state suppliers are not eligible.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-6. Eligible materials and quantities.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Sheathing and framing:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) OSB or plywood, four feet by 8 feet sheets;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Roof sheathing: 76 sheets;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Wall sheathing: 43 sheets;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(C) Subfloor, three-quarter inch T and G if used: 55 sheets; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(D) Total maximum: 174 sheets.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Dimensional lumber, two inches by four-inches, eight feet equivalent, up to a maximum of 475 pieces.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Roof trusses, stock trusses: Up to a maximum of 35 trusses whether roof trusses, stock trusses, or a combination of the two.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Roofing:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Up to a maximum of 22 squares of Asphalt shingles or 24 square metal roofing panels; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Up to a maximum of three rolls of roofing underlayment;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Up to a maximum of two rolls at 36-inches width of ice and water shield; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Up to a maximum of 23 pieces of 10-foot lengths of Drip edge.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Exterior finish:</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Siding: up to a maximum of 14 squares;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Housewrap:&nbsp;up to a maximum of two rolls;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Soffit:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 350 square feet; and</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Fascia and exterior trim, 10 feet lengths:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 31 pieces</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Foundation, if constructed: If a basement or foundation is constructed, the following quantities apply.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Concrete masonry units, 8 inches by 8 inches by 16 inches:&nbsp;up to a maximum 1,700 blocks;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Mortar, Type S,&nbsp;80-pound bags:&nbsp;up to a maximum 130 bags;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Reinforcing bar, No. 4, one-half inch diameter, 20 feet lengths:&nbsp;up to a maximum 40 sticks; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Anchor bolts, on-half inch by 10 inches:&nbsp;up to a maximum 30 units;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Basement finishing materials are not eligible.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) Drywall and finishes:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Drywall, four feet by 12 feet sheets:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 135 sheets;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Joint compound, four and one-half gallon buckets:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 30 buckets;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Drywall tape, 500 feet rolls:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 12 rolls; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Corner bead, 10-foot lengths:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 31 pieces.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) Flooring: Finished flooring materials, up to a maximum of 1,760 square feet</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(g) Paint and sealants:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Interior paint, one-gallon cans:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 36 gallons;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Primer, one-gallon cans:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 14 gallons;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Interior caulk, 10.1 ounce tubes:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 50 tubes; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Exterior sealant, 10.1 ounce tubes:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 20 tubes.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(h) Electrical and communications:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Breaker panel, 200 amp, 40 space:&nbsp;1 unit;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Standard receptacles including USB receptacles:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 42 units;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) GFCI receptacles:&nbsp;up to a maximum of six units;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Switches:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 22 units;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Light fixtures, interior and exterior combined:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 16 fixtures; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) NM cable:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Up to a maximum of 2,800 feet of 12-2;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Up to a maximum of 1,500 feet of 14-2;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(C) Up to a maximum of 250 feet of 12-3 or 10-3; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(D) Up to a maximum of&nbsp;500 feet of Internet cable, Cat 6.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(i) Plumbing</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) PEX pipe</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 300 feet of one-half inch;&nbsp;and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 80 feet of three-quarter inch.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) DWV pipe</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 60 feet of &nbsp;three-inch pipe;&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 85 feet of two-inch pipe; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(C) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 40 feet of one and one-half inch pipe; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Up to a maximum of&nbsp; 115 fittings DWV fittings.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(j) One of each of the following fixtures and appliances: toilet; tub shower unit; bathroom sink; kitchen sink; stove or range; dishwasher; refrigerator; furnace, air handler, or heat pump; and water heater.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(k) Windows and doors:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Standard stock size windows:&nbsp;up to a maximum of 11 units, including up to two picture windows, stock size&nbsp;60 inches by 72 inches;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Exterior doors, pre-hung stock,&nbsp;36 inches by 80 inches: up to a maximum of&nbsp;three units; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Interior doors, stock sizes:&nbsp;up to a maximum of&nbsp; nine units.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(l) Insulation:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Walls may have up to a maximum of 10 batt bundles or 36 cellulose bags;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Attics may have up to a maximum of 27 batt bundles or 50 cellulose bags.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-7. Subcontractors and affidavits.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Concrete, masonry, electrical, plumbing, and drywall work may be subcontracted. Any subcontractor supplying eligible materials shall submit an affidavit attesting that the materials were purchased from in state suppliers and incorporated into the eligible modest dwelling.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-8. Penalties.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Any builder or subcontractor who knowingly submits false documentation:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Shall repay the full rebate;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Shall pay a civil penalty equal to 200 percent of the rebate;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) May be barred from participation for 36 months; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Is guilty of a misdemeanor and may be fined $1,000 to $10,000 per violation.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-9. Rule making and administration.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The State Tax Commissioner shall propose legislative rules to administer this article, including:</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Creating application forms and affidavits;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Establishing documentation standards;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Conducting or contracting inspections of completed homes;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Audit procedures and enforcement actions; and</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) Appeals and corrective action procedures.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-15C-10. Effective date.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall take effect on July 1, 2026.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to create a state sales tax rebate for qualifying materials used in the construction of modest homes of 1,600 square feet or less, to limit the rebate to the state six percent sales tax, to permit voluntary municipal participation, to establish fixed material quantity limits.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


